@baseURL = http://localhost:6969
@urlPath = api/v1

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FULL FEATURE WALKTHROUGH
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# SETUP:
#   1. Start the server:           npm run start:dev
#   2. Run the seed script:        node scripts/seed.mjs --userId=<your-uuid>
#   3. Complete § 0 (Auth) to get tokens, paste them in VARIABLES below.
#   4. Paste the IDs printed by the seed script into the VARIABLES section.
#   5. Run each request top-to-bottom.
#
# SECTIONS:
#   § 0  Auth        — signup → verify-email → signin → refresh → signout
#   § 1  Goals       — CRUD + goal tree + nesting limits
#   § 2  Tasks       — CRUD + daily planner + status transitions + completion
#   § 3  Sessions    — manual entry + history queries  (WS notes included)
#   § 4  Habits      — CRUD + pause/resume + due-today + occurrences + analytics
#   § 5  Analytics   — dashboard + daily + weekly + goals + estimation
#   § 6  Error cases — expected 4xx per module
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── VARIABLES — fill these in before running ──────────────────────────────────
@token        = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

# IDs printed by seed.mjs:
@g1Id        = 6376f043-e4c0-48fd-a30c-d8e1f48338dc
@g2Id        = 96d75773-c232-41c7-abb8-8e156210fece
@g3Id        = bf28f03b-d9a9-42d1-8f67-1d8e04b37246
@g4Id        = 469b4143-51ce-4170-890f-da69335b42fa

@h1Id        = 3df5dafc-aa8f-48e9-869f-a63613cb7ecc
@h2Id        = d3fffdad-24ad-4848-a7fb-fc5e706304a2

@taskToday1  = 7be67d51-6c94-4113-80b6-2183fe7e2878
@taskToday2  = ccca6bc4-f5ba-4e19-acc4-a44dc6f5fc3b
@taskInbox   = 193a8bbb-d643-400f-8619-93c52ac1fc4c

# Filled in as you run through the steps:
@newGoalId        = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_1_1
@newTaskId        = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_2_1
@sessionId        = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_3_1
@newHabitId       = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_4_6
@occurrenceId     = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_4_5a
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 0  AUTH
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# NOTE: OAuth flows (Google / GitHub) must be opened in a browser — they are
#       redirect-based and cannot be driven from a REST client.
#       GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/google
#       GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/github

# ─── 0.1  Sign up ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Creates an account and sends a 6-char hex verification token to the email.
# Check your inbox (or Ethereal: https://ethereal.email) for the token.

### [0.1] POST auth/signup — register a new user
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.doe@ethereal.email",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstname": "Jane",
  "lastname": "Doe"
}

###

# ─── 0.2  Verify email ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Paste the 6-char token from the verification email into "token" below.
# On success you receive accessToken + refreshToken (you are now signed in).

### [0.2] POST auth/verify-email — confirm email address
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.doe@ethereal.email",
  "token": "PASTE_6_CHAR_TOKEN"
}

###

# ─── 0.3  Sign in ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Returns accessToken + refreshToken.
# Copy accessToken → @token above.
# Copy refreshToken → @refreshToken above.

### [0.3] POST auth/signin — local email + password
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jazmyn.kunze@ethereal.email",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

# ─── 0.4  Refresh tokens ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses the refresh token to issue a new access+refresh pair.
# Send the refreshToken (not the accessToken) in the Authorization header.

### [0.4] POST auth/refresh — rotate token pair
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{refreshToken}}

###

# ─── 0.5  Sign out ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Revokes the stored refresh token.  Subsequent refresh calls will 401.

### [0.5] POST auth/signout — invalidate session
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/signout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 1  GOALS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── 1.1  Create a new top-level goal ────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the returned `id` → paste into @newGoalId above.

### [1.1] POST goals — create top-level goal
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Ship a SaaS MVP",
  "description": "Complete the backend and a minimal frontend for a productivity app.",
  "category": "CAREER",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "deadline": "2026-12-31T23:59:59.000Z",
  "estimatedHours": 300
}

###

# ─── 1.2  Create a sub-goal under the seeded top-level goal ──────────────────

### [1.2] POST goals — create sub-goal (level 2 under g1)
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Study Advanced TypeScript Patterns",
  "category": "LEARNING",
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "estimatedHours": 20,
  "parentGoalId": "{{g1Id}}"
}

###

# ─── 1.3  Get full goal tree ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: the tree is served at GET /goals (not /goals/tree).
# Each node includes a `children` array. Results are Redis-cached (30 s TTL).

### [1.3] GET goals — full hierarchy for the authenticated user
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 1.4  List goals with filters ────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1.4a] GET goals — ACTIVE goals only
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals?status=ACTIVE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [1.4b] GET goals — LEARNING category
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals?category=LEARNING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 1.5  Get a single goal ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1.5] GET goals/:id
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/{{g2Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 1.6  Update a goal ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1.6] PATCH goals/:id — update estimatedHours + description
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/{{g2Id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "estimatedHours": 50,
  "description": "Cover every page of the official NestJS documentation with working examples."
}

###

# ─── 1.7  Pause then reactivate a goal ───────────────────────────────────────

### [1.7a] PATCH goals/:id — pause
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/{{g4Id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "PAUSED"
}

###

### [1.7b] PATCH goals/:id — reactivate
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/{{g4Id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "ACTIVE"
}

###

# ─── 1.8  Soft-delete a goal ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1.8] DELETE goals/:id — soft-delete the goal created in 1.1
DELETE {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/{{newGoalId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 2  TASKS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── 2.1  Create a new task ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the returned `id` → paste into @newTaskId above.

### [2.1] POST tasks — PLANNED task linked to a goal
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Build the analytics controller",
  "description": "Implement all 9 endpoints per the spec.",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "type": "PLANNED",
  "scheduledFor": "2026-03-01T09:00:00.000Z",
  "estimatedDuration": 90,
  "goalId": "{{g2Id}}"
}

###

# ─── 2.2  Create an unplanned (inbox) task ───────────────────────────────────

### [2.2] POST tasks — UNPLANNED task (no scheduledFor, no goal)
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Reply to design feedback email",
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "type": "UNPLANNED",
  "estimatedDuration": 15
}

###

# ─── 2.3  Daily planner queries ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2.3a] GET tasks?date=today — today's planned tasks (Redis-cached)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks?date=2026-03-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [2.3b] GET tasks?type=UNPLANNED — inbox / unplanned tasks
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks?type=UNPLANNED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [2.3c] GET tasks?type=PLANNED&goalId=… — all planned tasks under a goal
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks?type=PLANNED&goalId={{g2Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [2.3d] GET tasks?type=UNPLANNED&status=PENDING — pending inbox items
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks?type=UNPLANNED&status=PENDING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 2.4  Get a single task ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2.4] GET tasks/:id
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{taskToday1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 2.5  Update a task ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2.5] PATCH tasks/:id — reschedule + change estimatedDuration
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{newTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "estimatedDuration": 120,
  "scheduledFor": "2026-03-02T09:00:00.000Z"
}

###

# ─── 2.6  Status transitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2.6a] PATCH tasks/:id — PENDING → IN_PROGRESS (start working on it)
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{newTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}

###

### [2.6b] PATCH tasks/:id — IN_PROGRESS → PENDING (pause / back to queue)
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{newTaskId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "PENDING"
}

###

### [2.6c] PATCH tasks/:id — PENDING → CANCELLED
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{taskInbox}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "CANCELLED"
}

###

# ─── 2.7  Complete a task (triggers analytics + habit workers) ───────────────
# Fires:  COMPUTE_DAILY + COMPUTE_GOAL + UPDATE_ESTIMATION (analytics queue)
#         RECOMPUTE_GOAL_PROGRESS (goals queue)
#         MARK_HABIT_OCCURRENCE  (if habitId is set on the task)

### [2.7] PATCH tasks/:id/complete — mark as COMPLETED with actual duration
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{taskToday1}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "actualDuration": 65
}

###

# ─── 2.8  Delete a task ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2.8] DELETE tasks/:id — soft-delete the task created in 2.1
DELETE {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{newTaskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 3  SESSIONS (REST/manual — WebSocket events documented below)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# WebSocket namespace:  ws://localhost:6969/sessions
#
# 1. Connect:
#      { auth: { token: "<accessToken>" } }
#    On success the server emits `sessionResume` if an in-flight session exists.
#
# 2. Start a session:
#      emit  → "startSession"     { taskId: "<uuid>" }
#      recv  ← "sessionStarted"   { sessionId, taskId, startedAt, ... }
#
# 3. Keep-alive (every 30 s):
#      emit  → "heartbeat"        { sessionId: "<uuid>" }
#      recv  ← "heartbeatAck"     { sessionId, elapsedMs, plantGrowthPercent }
#
# 4. Log a distraction:
#      emit  → "logDistraction"   { sessionId, reason, estimatedMinutes }
#      recv  ← "distractionLogged" { distractions, plantStatus }
#
# 5. Stop a session (triggers analytics workers):
#      emit  → "stopSession"      { sessionId: "<uuid>" }
#      recv  ← "sessionStopped"   { sessionId, durationMinutes, netFocusMinutes,
#                                   distractionCount, plantStatus, plantGrowthPercent }

# ─── 3.1  Log a manual session ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the returned `id` → paste into @sessionId above.

### [3.1] POST sessions/manual — log a past focus block
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/manual
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "taskId": "{{taskToday2}}",
  "durationMinutes": 32,
  "startedAt": "2026-02-28T07:00:00.000Z",
  "note": "Morning run before breakfast"
}

###

# ─── 3.2  List sessions for a task ───────────────────────────────────────────

### [3.2] GET sessions/task/:taskId — all sessions for a given task
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/task/{{taskToday2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 3.3  Get a single session ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### [3.3] GET sessions/:id
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 3.4  Log another manual session to build daily analytics data ───────────

### [3.4] POST sessions/manual — second session today → creates time-leak data
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/manual
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "taskId": "{{taskToday1}}",
  "durationMinutes": 60,
  "startedAt": "2026-03-01T09:00:00.000Z",
  "note": "Deep NestJS study block"
}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 4  HABITS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── 4.1  List all habits ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4.1] GET habits — all habits for the user
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.2  Filter habits by goal ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4.2] GET habits?goalId=… — habits under a specific goal
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits?goalId={{g4Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.3  Get a single habit ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4.3a] GET habits/:id — daily habit
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [4.3b] GET habits/:id — specific-days habit
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h2Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.4  Today's due habits (daily planner feed) ────────────────────────────

### [4.4] GET habits/due-today — occurrences due on today's date
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/due-today
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.5  Occurrence history for a habit ──────────────────────────────────────
# Copy an occurrence `id` from the response → paste into @occurrenceId above.

### [4.5a] GET habits/:id/occurrences — all occurrences (seeded)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}/occurrences
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [4.5b] GET habits/:id/occurrences?status=COMPLETED — only completed
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}/occurrences?status=COMPLETED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [4.5c] GET habits/:id/occurrences?status=PENDING — today's pending
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}/occurrences?status=PENDING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.6  Create a new habit ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the returned `id` → paste into @newHabitId above.

### [4.6] POST habits — weekend reading habit
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "goalId": "{{g2Id}}",
  "title": "Weekend reading — tech articles",
  "description": "1 hour of reading Hacker News / dev blogs.",
  "frequency": "specific_days",
  "daysOfWeek": [0, 6],
  "targetDuration": 60
}

###

# ─── 4.7  Update a habit ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4.7] PATCH habits/:id — increase targetDuration for daily habit
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "targetDuration": 75,
  "description": "75 min focused NestJS / TS study block."
}

###

# ─── 4.8  Pause and resume a habit ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Pausing stops new occurrences from being generated.
# Resuming re-activates the habit.

### [4.8a] PATCH habits/:id/pause — pause the new weekend habit
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{newHabitId}}/pause
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [4.8b] PATCH habits/:id/resume — resume it again
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{newHabitId}}/resume
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.9  Complete an occurrence ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# durationMinutes must be >= targetDuration * 0.8 (20% grace window).
# Triggers async streak recalculation.

### [4.9] PATCH habits/:id/occurrences/:occurrenceId/complete
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}/occurrences/{{occurrenceId}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "durationMinutes": 62,
  "note": "Felt really focused today."
}

###

# ─── 4.10  Skip an occurrence ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Skipped occurrences do NOT break the streak.

### [4.10] PATCH habits/:id/occurrences/:occurrenceId/skip
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h2Id}}/occurrences/{{occurrenceId}}/skip
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 4.11  Habit-specific analytics ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Returns completion rate, average duration, streaks, and day-of-week miss
# patterns over the last 30 days.

### [4.11] GET habits/:id/analytics — analytics for daily habit
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{h1Id}}/analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [4.12] DELETE habits/:id — archive (soft-delete) the weekend habit
DELETE {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/habits/{{newHabitId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 5  ANALYTICS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# The seed script pre-computes all analytics documents, so every endpoint
# should return data immediately.
#
# Analytics are ALSO recomputed automatically when:
#   • A session ends   → COMPUTE_DAILY + COMPUTE_GOAL
#   • A task completes → COMPUTE_DAILY + COMPUTE_GOAL + UPDATE_ESTIMATION
#   • Every Sunday 23:00 UTC → COMPUTE_WEEKLY_ALL (fan-out)

# ─── 5.1  Dashboard (composite — all in one call) ────────────────────────────

### [5.1] GET analytics/dashboard — today + this week + all goals + estimation
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 5.2  Daily analytics ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [5.2a] GET analytics/daily?date=today
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/daily?date=2026-03-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.2b] GET analytics/daily?date= — a past day with a time leak
# Day 12 ago had two sessions with a break > 30 min
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/daily?date=2026-02-17
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.2c] GET analytics/daily/range — full February heatmap data
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/daily/range?startDate=2026-02-01&endDate=2026-03-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 5.3  Weekly analytics ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [5.3a] GET analytics/weekly?weekStart= — this week (Mon Feb 23)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/weekly?weekStart=2026-02-23
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.3b] GET analytics/weekly?weekStart= — last week (Mon Feb 16)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/weekly?weekStart=2026-02-16
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.3c] GET analytics/weekly/recent — last 4 weeks
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/weekly/recent?limit=4
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.3d] GET analytics/weekly/recent — default 8 weeks
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/weekly/recent
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 5.4  Goal analytics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [5.4a] GET analytics/goals — all goals (seeded: 4 documents)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/goals
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.4b] GET analytics/goals/:goalId — top-level NestJS goal (logged the most minutes)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/goals/{{g2Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5.4c] GET analytics/goals/:goalId — health goal
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/goals/{{g4Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 5.5  Estimation profile ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# rollingAverage > 100 → finishing faster than estimated
# rollingAverage < 100 → consistently over-running
# trend: IMPROVING | DECLINING | STABLE

### [5.5] GET analytics/estimation — rolling 30-task accuracy profile
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/estimation
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § 6  ERROR CASES  (each should return the stated HTTP status code)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── 401 — missing / invalid token ───────────────────────────────────────────

### [6.1] ❌ 401 — GET goals without token
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals

###

# ─── 400 — validation failures ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### [6.2] ❌ 400 — POST goals — missing required 'category'
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "This is missing category"
}

###

### [6.3] ❌ 400 — POST tasks — missing required 'estimatedDuration'
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "No duration set",
  "type": "PLANNED"
}

###

### [6.4] ❌ 400 — GET analytics/daily — bad date format (DD-MM-YYYY instead of YYYY-MM-DD)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/daily?date=01-03-2026
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [6.5] ❌ 400 — POST sessions/manual — missing durationMinutes
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/manual
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "taskId": "{{taskToday2}}"
}

###

### [6.6] ❌ 400 — GET tasks — no query params at all (requires at least one)
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 404 — not found ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [6.7] ❌ 404 — GET goals/:id — non-existent ID
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [6.8] ❌ 404 — GET analytics/daily — date with no activity
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/analytics/daily?date=2000-01-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [6.9] ❌ 404 — GET sessions/:id — non-existent session
GET {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/sessions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ─── 409 / 400 — domain rule violations ──────────────────────────────────────

### [6.10] ❌ 400 — POST goals — nesting depth > 3 levels
# g3 is already level 3; nesting under it must be rejected
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/goals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "This should be rejected — level 4",
  "category": "LEARNING",
  "parentGoalId": "{{g3Id}}"
}

###

### [6.11] ❌ 400 — PATCH tasks/:id/complete — task is already COMPLETED
PATCH {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/tasks/{{taskToday1}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "actualDuration": 30
}

###

### [6.12] ❌ 409 — POST auth/signup — email already registered
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jazmyn.kunze@ethereal.email",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstname": "John",
  "lastname": "Doe"
}

###

### [6.13] ❌ 401 — POST auth/signin — wrong password
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jazmyn.kunze@ethereal.email",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### [6.14] ❌ 401 — POST auth/verify-email — invalid token
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jazmyn.kunze@ethereal.email",
  "token": "000000"
}

###

### [6.15] ❌ 401 — POST auth/refresh — after signout (revoked token)
POST {{baseURL}}/{{urlPath}}/auth/refresh
Authorization: Bearer {{refreshToken}}

